'''😂'''（[[Unicode|Unicode]]：U+1F602）是一個象徵含淚大笑的[[繪文字|繪文字]]，中文地区或称之为「笑哭」<ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=“笑哭”符号成本年度全球最受欢迎表情|url=http://news.sina.com.cn/o/2016-12-04/doc-ifxyhwyy0610781.shtml|website=新浪新闻中心|accessdate=2019-11-08|language=zh-cn|archive-date=2019-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108152150/http://news.sina.com.cn/o/2016-12-04/doc-ifxyhwyy0610781.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>、「喜极而泣」<ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=牛津年度词汇 喜极而泣表情符号胜出|url=https://www.zaobao.com.sg/wencui/social/story20151118-550252|website=早报|accessdate=2019-11-08|language=zh-sg|archive-date=2019-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108152148/https://www.zaobao.com.sg/wencui/social/story20151118-550252|dead-url=no}}</ref>、「飙泪笑」或「笑到飙泪」<ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=牛津年度風雲字：笑到飆淚表情符號|url=https://www.cw.com.tw/article/article.action?id=5072489|website=天下雜誌|accessdate=2019-11-08|language=zh-tw|archive-date=2016-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702005333/http://www.cw.com.tw/article/article.action?id=5072489|dead-url=no}}</ref>等等。

==形象==
该[[绘文字|绘文字]]正式名称为“'''含泪大笑的脸'''”（{{lang|en|Face with Tears of Joy}}），外观通常为一张黄色的笑脸，其中双眼的部分眯成了两道线，两侧还挂着眼泪。嘴部笑得大咧，露出上牙（但在某些平台上会渲染成两排牙齿全都露出的样子）。<ref name=emojipedia>{{cite web|title=😂 Face With Tears of Joy Emoji|url=https://emojipedia.org/face-with-tears-of-joy/|website=Emojipedia|accessdate=2017-07-26|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706022116/http://emojipedia.org/face-with-tears-of-joy/|archivedate=2017-07-06|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref name=iemoji>{{cite web|title=Face with Tears of Joy Emoji (U+1F602)|url=http://www.iemoji.com/view/emoji/26/smileys-people/face-with-tears-of-joy|website=www.iemoji.com|accessdate=2017-07-26|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119063209/http://www.iemoji.com/view/emoji/26/smileys-people/face-with-tears-of-joy|archivedate=2016-11-19|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

==历史==
该表情最开始是由[[软银|软银]]等日本运营商所制作。<!--后来[[苹果公司|苹果公司]]在iOS 2.2开始也在系统中加入了该表情。--><ref name=iemoji />2010年，[[Unicode|Unicode 6.0]]引入了该表情，对应的编码为U+1F602。2013年，数据分析公司{{link-en|Luminoso}}发表报告，称其在[[推特|推特]]上的使用量已经超过了[[波浪号|波浪号]]。<ref name=wired>{{cite web|last1=McHugh|first1=Molly|title=Face With Tears of Joy is the internet’s favorite emoji by a landslide|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/12/time-shouldve-made-the-tears-of-joy-emoji-person-of-the-year/|website=WIRED|accessdate=2017-07-26|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321015705/https://www.wired.com/2015/12/time-shouldve-made-the-tears-of-joy-emoji-person-of-the-year/|archivedate=2017-03-21|language=en|date=2017-03-21|deadurl=yes}}</ref>2015年，Emoji 1.0加入了该表情。<ref name=emojipedia />它是2015年全球使用次数最多的绘文字，占美国当年绘文字总使用量的17%、英国的20%。<ref name=ox />

==评价==
2015年，《[[牛津词典|牛津词典]]》将该表情选为“2015年度词汇”——这也是年度词汇中首次出现绘文字。<ref name=ox>{{cite web|title=Oxford Dictionaries Word of the Year 2015 is… {{!}} OxfordWords blog|url=http://blog.oxforddictionaries.com/2015/11/word-of-the-year-2015-emoji/|website=OxfordWords blog|accessdate=2017-07-26|date=2015-11-16|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710101430/http://blog.oxforddictionaries.com/2015/11/word-of-the-year-2015-emoji/|archivedate=2017-07-10|deadurl=yes}}</ref>有些人评论道，其用途宽泛，不仅仅是局限在了原设计师所设想的“喜极而泣”，而是衍生出了嘲讽、强调等作用，<ref>{{cite web|last1=Waldman|first1=Katy|title=This Year's Word of the Year Isn't Even a Word 😂😂😂|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/lexicon_valley/2015/11/16/the_face_with_tears_of_joy_emoji_is_the_word_of_the_year_says_oxford_dictionaries.html|website=Slate|accessdate=2017-07-26|date=2015-11-16|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161204031738/http://www.slate.com/blogs/lexicon_valley/2015/11/16/the_face_with_tears_of_joy_emoji_is_the_word_of_the_year_says_oxford_dictionaries.html|archivedate=2016-12-04|deadurl=yes}}</ref>甚至有时人们不清楚自己为何要使用这一表情，<ref>{{cite web|last1=O'Connor|first1=Amy|title=The cry laughing emoji needs to be stopped — here’s why|url=http://www.dailyedge.ie/cry-laughing-emoji-worst-emoji-2361456-Oct2015/|website=The Daily Edge|accessdate=2017-07-26|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318110506/http://www.dailyedge.ie/cry-laughing-emoji-worst-emoji-2361456-Oct2015/|archivedate=2017-03-18|deadurl=yes}}</ref>或者只是想要简单地应和一声。<ref name = TheTab />《[[连线|连线]]》认为，比起大部分严肃的表情来说，它更为生动活泼，表达意思时也更为准确。<ref name=wired />

对该表情的理解有好有坏。《[[科学美国人|科学美国人]]》认为它表达出友好、积极的意思，适用于“任何希望寻求一致的对话交流”当中，有助于缓和双方的情绪。<ref>{{cite web|last1=D'Costa|first1=Krystal|title=Why Is the "Tears of Joy" Emoji Everywhere?|url=https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/anthropology-in-practice/why-is-the-tears-of-joy-emoji-everywhere/|website=Scientific American Blog Network|accessdate=2017-07-26|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170110041618/https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/anthropology-in-practice/why-is-the-tears-of-joy-emoji-everywhere/|archivedate=2017-01-10|language=en|deadurl=yes}}</ref>也有人对此持相反态度。《[[卫报|卫报]]》发表评论称它是“最糟糕的绘文字”，因为它表露出“嘲弄、揶揄的神态，天生便是残忍的模样”，可被视作一种人身攻击。<ref>{{cite news|title=The ‘tears of joy’ emoji is the worst of all – it’s used to gloat about human suffering|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/nov/24/tears-of-joy-emoji-worst-gloat-about-human-suffering|website=The Guardian|accessdate=2017-07-26|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170624083905/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/nov/24/tears-of-joy-emoji-worst-gloat-about-human-suffering|archivedate=2017-06-24|date=2016-11-24|language=en|deadurl=yes}}</ref>The Tab认为它“很烦”、充斥在互联网的各处，并呼吁人们减少使用。<ref name=TheTab>{{cite web|title=We should have left the crying/laughing emoji in 2015|url=https://thetab.com/2016/03/02/the-cryinglaughing-emoji-makes-you-look-like-an-idiot-77855|website=The Tab|accessdate=2017-07-26|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161127045025/http://thetab.com/2016/03/02/the-cryinglaughing-emoji-makes-you-look-like-an-idiot-77855|archivedate=2016-11-27|date=2016-03-02|language=en|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

